Whoa Whoa Whoa. This one caught my attention Fink. That's a lot of truth packed into 1 amazing article! What are the lessons we can all implement NOW? (head in the sand is not an option) 

"Perhaps the most jaw-dropping sign of the times: Salesforce’s CEO Marc Benioff just froze all engineering hires for 2025, citing the “success of AI agents” that can do the work of coders (Marc Benioff says Salesforce will hire no engineers this year). In his words, today’s business leaders may be “the last generation to manage only humans." When the guy who runs San Francisco’s largest tech employer says “AI is gobbling up engineering jobs," you know white-collar workers are officially on notice."

@brianfink
